# Undo last commit + Keep files	    : git reset --soft HEAD~1
# Undo last commit + Delete files	: git reset --hard HEAD~1
# Delete commit from middle	        : git rebase -i Head~3 (Find the line for the commit you want to remove and change the word pick to drop)
# Save the file and close the file
# Update GitHub after deletion    	: git push --force (as the file you update cloned the commits from remote but no to make changes on remote you hve to execute the push force command )
